AVIAN INFLUENZA (67): CHINA (HONG KONG) PET BIRDS, HPAI H5N6, OIE
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 16 Apr 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited] http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=26434


Highly pathogenic influenza A viruses (infection with) (non-poultry including wild birds), Hong Kong (SAR - PRC)
----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 Apr 2018 from Dr. Thomas Sit, Chief Veterinary Officer/Assistant Director (Inspection & Quarantine), Agriculture, Fisheries and Conservation Department, Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Government, Hong Kong, (SAR-PRC)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 7 Apr 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 12 Apr 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 4 Apr 2018
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza A [AI] virus
Serotype: H5N6
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Yuen Po Street Bird Garden, Mong Kok, Yau Tsim Mong District, Hong Kong
Date of start of the outbreak: 7 Apr 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: other
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Birds / 2834 / 1 / 0 / 2834 / 0

Affected population: A sample collected from a bird cage holding Hill Mynas in a pet bird shop on [7 Apr 2018] tested positive for H5N6 highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI) virus.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Birds / 0.04 / 0 / 0 / 100
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: An avian influenza intensive surveillance system is in place for all poultry farms, poultry markets, and pet bird shops in Hong Kong. A sample collected from a pet bird shop during routine surveillance on [7 Apr 2018] tested positive for H5N6 highly pathogenic influenza A virus. A total of 2834 pet birds were removed from the shop, culled, and disposed of on [13 Apr 2018]. The Yuen Po Street Bird Garden, where the pet bird shop was located, will be closed for 21 days. No spread of disease is evident. Neither the Hong Kong Wetland Park nor Mai Po Nature Reserve nor any poultry farms are located within 3 km of the outbreak location.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, screening, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste, stamping out, zoning, disinfection, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists), no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Tai Lung Veterinary Laboratory, Agriculture, Fisheries & Conservation Department (National laboratory) / Birds / real-time reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 12 Apr 2018 / Positive
Tai Lung Veterinary Laboratory, Agriculture, Fisheries & Conservation Department (National laboratory) / Birds / virus isolation / 12 Apr 2018 / Positive
Centre of Influenza Research, School of Public Health, Li Ka Shing Faculty of Medicine, University of Hong Kong (regional reference laboratory) / Birds / gene sequencing / [not available] / Pending
National Influenza Centre, Centre for Health Protection, Department of Health (Regional Reference Laboratory) / Birds / gene sequencing / [not available] / Pending

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In addition to this new event, since January 2018 to date, Hong Kong has reported another 3 events associated with HPAI H5N6. The situation for each of these events is as follows:

1. Event started 18 Jan 2018; one outbreak reported (a sample of oropharyngeal swabs from imported chilled chickens); the event was resolved. See event summary and updated map: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=25693.

2. Event started 7 Feb 2018; one outbreak reported in a wild bird (black-headed gull); the event was resolved. See event summary and updated map: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=25925.

3. Event started 4 Apr 2018; one outbreak reported in a wild bird (crested myna); the event is still continuing. See event summary and updated map: http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=26389. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Hong Kong: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5751372,198]
